# ========================================
# QURI Protocol - Environment Variables
# ========================================

# Application URL (for metadata and OG images)
# Development: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://your-domain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Internet Computer Configuration
# For playground/production: https://ic0.app
# For local development: http://localhost:4943
NEXT_PUBLIC_IC_HOST=https://ic0.app
NEXT_PUBLIC_DFX_NETWORK=ic

# ========================================
# ICP Canister IDs
# ========================================
# Get these IDs after deploying canisters
# Quick start: Run ./scripts/deploy-playground.sh

# Core Canisters (required)
NEXT_PUBLIC_RUNE_ENGINE_CANISTER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_BITCOIN_INTEGRATION_CANISTER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_REGISTRY_CANISTER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_IDENTITY_MANAGER_CANISTER_ID=

# Backend Canisters (optional - when implemented)
NEXT_PUBLIC_DEX_CANISTER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_BRIDGE_CANISTER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_WRUNES_LEDGER_CANISTER_ID=

# Internet Identity (mainnet)
NEXT_PUBLIC_INTERNET_IDENTITY_CANISTER_ID=rdmx6-jaaaa-aaaaa-aaadq-cai

# Sign-in with Bitcoin (SIWB) Canister
# Deploy your own: https://github.com/AstroxNetwork/ic-siwb
# Required for Bitcoin wallet authentication
NEXT_PUBLIC_SIWB_CANISTER_ID=

# IPFS Storage (Pinata)
# Get your keys at: https://app.pinata.cloud/developers/api-keys
NEXT_PUBLIC_PINATA_API_KEY=your-pinata-api-key
NEXT_PUBLIC_PINATA_SECRET_KEY=your-pinata-secret-api-key

# NFT.Storage (Alternative/Primary IPFS Storage)
# Get your API key at: https://nft.storage/manage/
# IMPORTANT: Use the FULL API key (starts with eyJ...)
NEXT_PUBLIC_NFT_STORAGE_API_KEY=your-nft-storage-api-key

# Optional: Alternative IPFS Gateway
# NEXT_PUBLIC_IPFS_GATEWAY=https://gateway.pinata.cloud

# ========================================
# How to Get Canister IDs
# ========================================
#
# OPTION 1: Automated Script (Recommended) ‚ö°
# ------------------------------------------
# Run: ./scripts/deploy-playground.sh
# This will:
# - Deploy all canisters to ICP Playground
# - Automatically create frontend/.env.local with IDs
# - Show you the URLs to access canisters
#
# OPTION 2: Manual Deployment
# ----------------------------
# 1. Deploy to playground (free, 20 min expiry):
#    dfx deploy --playground
#
# 2. Get canister IDs:
#    dfx canister id rune-engine --playground
#    dfx canister id registry --playground
#    (repeat for each canister)
#
# 3. Copy this file to .env.local and add the IDs
#
# OPTION 3: Local Development
# ----------------------------
# 1. Start local replica:
#    dfx start --background --clean
#
# 2. Deploy locally:
#    dfx deploy
#
# 3. Get canister IDs:
#    dfx canister id rune-engine
#
# 4. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_IC_HOST=http://localhost:4943
#
# ========================================
# Vercel Deployment
# ========================================
#
# To deploy to Vercel with canister integration:
#
# 1. Deploy canisters first (use script or manual method above)
#
# 2. Add environment variables in Vercel:
#    a. Go to: https://vercel.com/dashboard
#    b. Select your QURI-PROTOCOL project
#    c. Go to: Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
#    d. Add each NEXT_PUBLIC_* variable
#    e. Choose environments: Production, Preview, Development
#
# 3. Redeploy:
#    - Push to GitHub (auto-deploy if enabled)
#    - Or run: vercel --prod
#
# 4. Test:
#    - Visit your Vercel URL
#    - Check browser console for canister connections
#
# ========================================
# Important Notes
# ========================================
#
# ‚ö†Ô∏è  Playground Limitations:
# - Canisters expire after 20 minutes
# - Free but temporary
